    <string name="text_readme">
    \nThis app does not install Linux on your phone. Instead it lets you know
    when updates are available for your computer’s Linux install.\n

    \nHave you installed Linux? Are you using an operating system like Debian 
    or Ubuntu? Would you like to know when your favorite program is ready to 
    update… Even before you start up your computer? Now you can use this app 
    to watch your favorite distro when it updates packages! \n
    
    \nREADME TEXT:\n
    \nInstructions (short version):\n
    \n 1. Start App
    \n 2. Configure URL of Distro on Configure page
    \n 3. Confirm URL Change and Click Pink \'go\' button
    \n 4. Browse Repository (\'BROWSE\' button on main page)
    \n 5. Click on files for tracking (checkbox will turn green when file is selected)
    \n 6. LATER: click on \'CONFIGURE\' and \'CHECK DISTRO\' to see if updates for your files are available.\n

    \nNOTES: The program just keeps one list of files for tracking, so if you switch the url you may
        still get notification that your package is new even though you selected it when another url
        was being used.\n
    \n\'CHECK DISTRO\' typically will not work immediately after URL is set. It will take some time
        for the distro developers to update the package repository. Then the \'CHECK DISTRO\' button
        will work. Be patient.

    </string>
